A BILL FORAN ACT
RELATING TO CULTURE AND ARTS.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that culture, arts, and
2 history are essential pillars of Hawaii's identity and are vital
3 to building vibrant, resilient, and connected communities. The
4 State has long supported these efforts through the state
5 foundation on culture and the arts, which plays an important
6 role in promoting the arts and expanding access for residents
7 statewide.
8 The legislature further finds that jurisdictions around the
9 world have advanced innovative, place-based strategies that
10 integrate culture, arts, and history into planning,
11 infrastructure, and community development, resulting in stronger
12 public spaces, increased economic activity, and more dynamic and
13 inclusive communities.
14 The legislature also finds that Hawaii can build upon its
15 existing foundation by expanding its capacity to support
16 creative community development, foster cross-sector
2026-2567 SB3007 GDI SMA.docx 1
lillinilHiirilBEIflBlllIQIil

