C.D. 1
1 collaboration, and advance projects that meaningfully integrate
2 culture and the arts into the fabric of everyday life.
3 Accordingly, the purpose of this Act is to establish the
4 office of community culture, arts, and innovation as a sister
5 entity to the state foundation on culture and the arts to
6 broaden and strengthen the State's creative portfolio. The
7 office shall identify and advance best practices; support state
8 agencies and community partners in implementing innovative,
9 place-based strategies; and prioritize projects that enhance
10 public spaces, strengthen community connections, and improve
11 quality of life across the State.
12 The office shall also establish a community and cultural
13 partnership program to serve as a resource for communities
14 statewide. The program shall support efforts that preserve and
15 elevate cultural and historical assets, stimulate social and
16 economic activity, and catalyze positive, community-driven
17- change, with projects serving as scalable models for replication
18 in other communities, as appropriate.
19 SECTION 2. Chapter 201, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
20 amended by adding a new part to be appropriately designated and
21 to read as follows:
