1 "FART OFFICE OF COMMUNITY CULTURE, ARTS, ARD INNOVATION
2 §201-A Definitions. As used in. this part:
3 "Executive director" means the executive director of the
4 office of community culture, arts, and innovation, appointed
5 pursuant to section 201-B{b).
6 "Office" means the office of community culture, arts, and
7 innovation established pursuant to section 201-B.
8 §201-B Office of community culture, arts, and innovation;
9 established; executive director. (a) There is established an
10 office of community culture, arts, and innovation within the
11 department of business, economic development, and tourism for
12 administrative purposes only.
13 (b) The office shall be headed by an executive director
14 who shall be appointed by the governor without regard to
15 chapter 76. Notwithstanding section 76-16(b) (17), the exemption
16 from chapter 76 under this subsection shall not expire.
17 (c) The executive director may employ staff for the office
18 without regard to chapters 76 and 89; provided that the staff
19 shall be members of the employees’ retirement system and shall
20 be eligible to receive the benefits of any employee benefit
21 program generally applicable to officers and employees of the
