1 State. Notwithstanding section 76-16(b) (17), the exemption from
2 chapter 76 under this subsection shall not expire.
3 (d) Department heads may temporarily assign additional
4 employees from existing positions within their departments to
5 the office; provided that the employees shall represent their
6 respective department's needs, assist other departments, or
7 otherwise support the needs of the office during the course of
8 their assignment with the office.
9 (e) The office may provide grants and contract for the
10 provision of programs and services to perform its functions and
11 duties pursuant to section 201-C.
12 §201-C Office of community culture, arts, and innovation;
13 functions and duties. The office shall:
14 (1) Execute projects and programs related to community
15 improvement as directed by the governor and
16 legislature;
17 (2) Support and assist other state departments and
18 agencies with creative and innovative improvements to
19 their projects, programs, and endeavors to add value
20 to communities;
