1 (3) Develop creative and innovative projects, programs,
2 and endeavors and pilot new approaches to add value to
3 communities, their culture, and quality of life;
4 (4) Identify creative and innovative best practices used
5 by other jurisdictions, assess their value to the
6 State, and innovate accordingly;
7 (5) Ensure communication with the state foundation on
8 culture and the arts regarding the office's functions
9 and duties for consistency and better planning for the
10 State; and
11 (6) Adopt rules in accordance with chapter 91 for the
12 purposes of this part.
13 §201-D Annual repost. The office shall submit an annual
14 report summarizing its activities during the preceding year to
15 the legislature no later than twenty days prior to the convening
16 of each regular session. The report shall include:
17 (1) Creative and innovative strategies proposed or
18 employed by other jurisdictions that the office has
19 identified that may have potential benefit for
20 communities in the State;
